Goal: build and verify FSCRUD-01 from a direct local-model prompt

memory:
  fscrud_workspace
  fscrud_task

flow:
  remember key="fscrud_workspace" value="workspace/fscrud-01"
  remember key="fscrud_task" value="TASK.md"

  run: node -e "const fs=require('fs'); fs.mkdirSync('workspace/fscrud-01',{recursive:true});" [timeout 60]
  let task_contract = "FSCRUD-01 field-service work order tracker. Build customers, assets, and work_orders with list/create/read/edit/detail/delete flows; enforce customer-asset-work_order references, asset/customer mismatch rejection, completedAt/status rules, safe deletes, seed data, domain validation tests, integration-style tests for each entity family, README, run-manifest.json, and verification-report.md. Full task source is TASK.md."

  prompt: Work only in ${fscrud_workspace}. Read ${fscrud_task} before editing. Task contract: ${task_contract}. Build a full-stack CRUD app with customers, assets, and work orders. Include validation, relationship integrity, UI list/create/edit/detail/delete flows, seed data, tests, README, run manifest, and verification report. Run install, test, and build or typecheck if available before stopping. Do not read or modify hidden verifier files. Local inference can be slow; prioritize correct, complete, verifiable work over speed.

done when:
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/package.json
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/README.md
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/run-manifest.json
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/verification-report.md
